dc_description_s: These data layers represent parks and open spaces for Rock County, Wisconsin in 2016. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, “Rock_Parks_OpenSpace_2016.gdb”. The features included in this geodatabase are “Rock_County_Federal_Lands”, “Rock_County_Park_Areas”, “Rock_County_Park_Points”, and “Rock_County_WDNR_Land”.[County_Park_Areas: This is an SDE feature class of Rock County Park Areas queried out of the Real Property Departments parcel maps of the County. This data has been edited to remove park areas that have been divested.County_Park_Points: This is a feature class of the Rock County Park location points. It was created in late 2002 as part of the Rock County Parks, Outdoor Recreation, and Open Space Plan. It was edited in April of 2005 to reflect the divestiture of Emerald Grove County Park in June of 2004.]
